reviews.text: Amazing experience! Would definitely visit again. Loads to see and learn about. The entire museum can seen in a couple hours. We were in Phoenix and it was a very scenic drive to the museum. The museum also has a trail. I do recommend long pants, tennis, and bug spray. Trail is not good for strollers so bring your baby carriers.

We always stop here when passing through Flagstaff for both the informative and always changing museum exhibits, and the carefully curated selections of Native American crafts in their gift shop. Always a pleasure and have picked up baskets and jewelry here over the years.

What a wonderful find up in Flagstaff, AZ!. We came upon this museum by accident. It was a wonderful way to spend the afternoon. Unfortunately, I didn't get the front desk lady's name but she was wonderful. She explained the layout of the museum and made our visit and experience exceptional. The displays are great and educational. Just a great experience.

Came here for a class project and was pleasantly surprised at how nice the exhibits were. I just love the new intro to -I believe- the 3rd exhibit on the map with the different Native American speakers welcoming visitors in their own language. Looking forward to bringing my mom when she visits this month!
What a wonderful museum! Learned a lot about geology, archeology and the most treasured heritage of native Americans, with my two girls. Well done!

Went to the Christmas tour. It was nice but a lot of walking and no heat so pretty cold in the winter. The history was great to learn about. Overall had a good time. If you have trouble walking a lot or standing in one spot for long then it may not be for you. There are also stairs.
Fascinating tour led by an extremely knowledgeable guide. With an interest in mission furniture and the arts and crafts movement, my partner and I found this a great stop on our vacation.

Loved seeing Riordan all decked out in Christmas. Our guide, John, was very knowledgeable and learned a few new things that I hadn't heard from a previous visit. I brought a friend/family member visiting from Nebraska and it was a perfect snowy day activity that brought Flagstaff's history to life.

Amazing historic park in Flagstaff. A must see for anyone visiting the town. Flagstaff, Lake Mary, Snowbowl and most things in the area owe their existence to the Riordan family. Seeing their house and experiencing the early 20th century lively hood is a fantastic experience. The one hour guided tour is extremely informative and entertaining.

Our tour guide Audrey was so sweet and great with the kids. We had a great time and  learned a ton. The grounds are beautiful especially in the winter, great place for kids to get some energy outside before doing the tour. It takes about an hour, but goes by fast with all the stuff to see.
Nice display on the history of the Airzona National guard
Great walk through history of the fort and 185th Inf, knowledgeable staff, adding to exhibits as they can.
A fantastic tour and history of the 158th IN Regiment and the Arizona National Guard
Small and only one building

Went there to see The Foundry performances.  Great place.  When heading out of town towards this place, be sure and look for the tiny sign on the right. The driveway is easy to miss and actually comes up sooner than the directions alert you to.  Maps took us to the next driveway anyway, and we had to turn around.
A great space dedicated to promoting and providing art to the Flagstaff Community and the Coconino region
great space for visual and performance art
Such a great place to visit. I always love the exhibits they have.
Nice building, but exhibit was a little thin... only 3 pieces to the Hidden Landscapes, but they were cool.

As I always try to something new, I tried this Chinese restaurant today. From outside, it looks like closed, because they covered the window fully and when i enter, no costumer there, only cashier. Not that nice environment, dominated by silence. Once I get in, he offered me to have a seat. Then I had a seat and ordered their Special Beef. The food was just so so. The beef really doesn’t taste, because he poured very sweet souse on it. Maybe it is just not my flavour.
We come here somewhat often.  The food is consistently delicious, as is the service. We love their vegetable delight with crispy rice... Yum!
Love this place! The owners are ALWAYS friendly as well as the staff. The food tastes great too!

This is the best place for Chinese that I have found in Flagstaff, hands down! The cream cheese crab rangoons were thick and creamy inside, and the homemade sweet and sour sauce was fantastic. The egg flower is perfection when you add just a bit of soy sauce, and the sesame chicken was lightly crispy and absolutely delicious. Great prices for the amount of food you receive. The lady owner is super sweet and provides great service! I highly recommend checking this place out.
Crab puffs were delicious, and their sweet and sour sauce is great too. The owner is super friendly and kind, with fast service and generous portions to boot. Will definitely be returning!
The food was delicious, and the waiter was outstanding. He always catered to us and made sure everything we needed, we got. He even took a picture of us! Would highly recommend.
I had takeout, and got the fried rice which was good. I also tried a friends soup and let me tell you it was delicious. I highly recommend for someone whose craving thai!
The service and food is wonderful.  One of the best Thai food place in town. Downtown location makes it hard for parking though. Keep that in mind
Attentive server, nice ambiance, tasty food. Among many Thai restaurants I’ve visited, I’d say this place is pretty good.
We walked in and it was super clean and we were greated with a smile. The decorations were beautiful and the food was amazing. 💖

Yummy Thai food.  Really liked the vegetable dish with beef.  The green curry was good.. definitely spicy like the menu says.  Pad Thai was very good.  The soup was good, but I missed one flavor I am used to, not sure what it was.  Environment was classy yet fun.  Interesting decorating combo...I liked it.

After crawling out of the bottom of the Grand Canyon we fled to Flagstaff in search of nourishment. For the last three days we'd eaten only dehydrated meals through the use of backpacking stoves. In other words we were HANGRY! Something refreshing was in order and the staff managed to accommodate our request for a party of 10 on a Friday at 6pm. Bravo! The drinks were cold and the food was tasty. The foods were easy to share and in the end we lulled our pallets into submission.
Best place ever will go here again. Best quality food and amazing customer service. Recommend others.

Good food and great service. Atmosphere was excellent and my wife and I enjoyed our meals (Chicken Pad Thai and Beef Spicy Noodles). Only critique I have is I would have like to see a bit more meat in both of the dishes.

This place was so good!! Would definitely come and dine again! I had the pinapinea curry and it was delicious! I got my curry mild for spicyness and it was hot. This is coming from someone who loves spicy food. Also had the Jasmine tea, quite delicious, so get the whole little pot to yourself 😊 Shout to the concerige at the Wyndham for the recommendation!

First time eating here and it won't be the last! The lady in the front was really nice and helpful. We ordered a pepperoni and mushroom pizza. It had a great crust and the toppings were fresh tasting. The pizza does take a little while to make so I'd suggest calling ahead to order. They do have a small area with a few tables for eating there.

If you're a person who loves toppings or a lot of cheese, this is probably not the best place for you. Ordered a sausage jalapeno pizza and a few slices only had one or two pieces of either. But besides that I have to say the pizza was quite delicious and the toppings that made it onto the pizza were delicious.
Best quality pizza in flagstaff hands down. Wait times can get high, but there is no rushing quality.

I really wanted to love this pizza.  It was supposed to come with all these local premium ingredients. My family gladly paid $80.00  for 2 12" pizzas and 2 16" pizzas hoping for a gormet pizza experience.  When the pizza was delivered 90 minutes after ordering there were very few pieces of pinapple and the bacon was so hard to find. There were two to three pieces of half inch square-sized pieces of chicken per slice.  And the cheese was limited at best.  We were just so disappointed.   I suppose we will have to go out and pick up Nimarco's pizza if we want the experience we were expecting.

This is the best pizza I've probably had. Tried both conventional and vegan here, both were great. The ginger soda they make is EASILY my favorite ginger soda thus far (and I love ginger soda/ginger beer - also, uses honey, so not vegan for those wondering). I've never eaten at a place that made me consider driving EIGHT HOURS to go to it again. Coming from someone all the way in San Diego county California, this is one of the best places I've eaten. I wish Google gave me one "six star" review a year. It would go to New Jersey Pizza.

We got in just before the rush.  Good thing we did, because within 45 minutes there was a line out the door!  The entire staff was FANTASTIC.  Server never let the beverages run out, she was pleasant and extremely prompt.  Based upon our order she gave us a great estimate of time. Food was wonderful. Everyone was timely, timely, timely.  GREAT JOB Oregano's!

Such a charming restaurant offering so much variety,amazing prices for kids meals and adults,huge portions and outstanding service,great quality food,they are so generous,other restaurants need to learn from them;) Decor here is fun to look at while you wait for a table. Staff were very friendly and attentive. Although it was a busy Friday night, the wait didn't seem long and they give samples of pizze while you wait in the lobby. The calamari, pizza and wings were all delicious. Our only regret was not having leftovers.

Ordered the pan pepperoni pizza and OH MY GOODNESS. Best pizza we have ever had hands down. We were completely astonished by how good it was. I've read reviews and heard from many that the pizza is good, and is it ever. We couldn't get enough! Thank you! ♡
Always a great experience.   I have always had good attentive service with a smile.  The food is consistently good.

We had a dinner for 8 catered by them yesterday and wow I was impressed.   Everything was packaged ready to serve.  They gave us plastic servicing tools and tons of garlic bread.   I honestly can’t believe how awesome it was and for the price.   Well done !   We will use you again !

We are from LA and are passing through on a six week roadie.  Found this restaurant through a google search of reviews.  We were NOT disappointed!  Welcomed by a bevy of employees, not too loud and the decor was purely Southwest.  The chairs are hand painted and carved with beautiful scenes of the Southwest.  The food rivals our favorite restaurant in L.A.  When in Flagstaff, this place is not to be missed.  Total bill for 2 adults and 3 kids $42.00

Not too shabby!

We were staying a night in Flagstaff and decided to try this restaurant. The service wasn't unfriendly but it certainly wasn't friendly. They took forever to take our drink order. Then it was 15 minutes before they brought them to us. They took another 15 minutes after that to take our food order and its not like they were packed. 4 tables maybe. The food was terrible. Even our kids wouldn't eat their food. Next trip, this place is out!

The food is fantastic! From the huge plate of nachos to the tacos, fajitas and the strong margaritas. ..this place is a favorite of mine and my family. The portions are huge and very resonalby priced and I always take a box home with me. Try this place out!
Fast service.  Everything we  ate was wonderful. We had burritos, queso, churros, fried ice cream, enchilada, and a tamale. The salsa is very good.
The service wasn't bad, but the food was awful.
The food is good but not outstanding. Good guacamole and sopapillas The bathroom needs serious updating and cleaning. They will accommodate special food requests for food sensitivities.

I ate here for the first time today and real talk, this place was great! The building itself, inside, seems a little dated. But, I didn't come for the decor or architecture. I came for the food and it did not disappoint. I had the choose three combo, having two ground beef tacos, hard shell, cheese enchilada, and the grilled skewered shrimp. The ice tea was refreshing too. And, to top it all off, the service was off the hook! From the hostess to the server to the bus staff, everyone treated us well and it was a very welcoming environment. We will be sure to return to this establishment in the future. I would suggest y'all give it a try for yourselves!
Excellent service.  Excellent food.  Always good.
Probably the best Mexican food I've had in a while and their margaritas are on point too!

My family has been coming here for years-even before I was born! They've changed a lot, especially their menu, but it's still delicious. It's definitely has a local, family vibe. It's great for big groups or small parties. Sometimes the wait can be a bit long when it's busy, but they're usually pretty fast when seating their guests. They don't have a lot of American options, so if you're not into Mexican-American food this might not be the place for you. HOWEVER, I highly recommend trying this local favorite out!

We went on a Tuesday morning, so I can't speak to the weekend crowds. I can say, however, that food was delicious and the atmosphere was awesome. The chilaquiles are as tasty as advertised and the coffee was solid. I loved the vibe and the artwork adorning the walls of the restaurant. Definite local vibe, well worth a visit to MartAnnes.

Went here for breakfast on our way home to Phoenix from a weekend in Flagstaff.  It was our best meal the entire weekend! Great fresh ingredients and good prices for portions.  The bloody mary even comes with a homemade jalapeno popper.  Great Mexican Food and beautiful decor.

It can’t be overstated how wonderful the chilaquiles are here. The only reason I didn’t leave five stars is because it is rather busy and somewhat tightly packed during morning hours. Regardless, the delicious food is worth the tight squeeze.

As always, the food was absolutely spectacular. The well-featured chilaquiles are always delightful, and today was no exception. Get them Christmas style and enjoy the best of both worlds! And make good use of the table salsa. It's absolutely fantastic and a wonderful accompaniment to the hash browns.

Best breakfast in Flag. Maybe best breakfast in Arizona. Maybe best breakfast in the southwest. (And so on and so forth until we reach "on earth".) Always a wait. Never parking. Awesome portions. Fresh squeezed juice. Good coffee. Warm atmosphere that's full of character. Go. There. Now.

First time I have ever been here.  It was a good experience.  The food was delicious.  The servers were friendly and polite and helpful.  The only thing lacking was the servers were overwhelmed with customers and didn't get back to our table as fast as I would have liked.  If there were a couple more servers to help out I think it would have gone smoother.  Other than that it's a great place to eat.  The prices are very good for all the food that you get.

Found this little restaurant on a recent trip “out west” with my friend. We enjoyed our breakfast so much that we came back the next day to eat here again! The food was delicious, the coffee was AMAZING, and the service was exceptional. At first glance it seemed to be a little on the pricey side for breakfast, but wow... the food! Sooo yummy! And the portions are quite large so two people could easily split a meal. I would definitely recommend Brandy’s to anyone traveling in the Flagstaff area.

Funky little restaurant in Flagstaff.  Found this because it was on Diners, Drive-ins and Dives.  Staff was fantastic.  Food was very good.  Had the potato/bacon/chile soup which was excellent.  The bagel was okay (probably good by western standards, but if your from the east like me, be forewarned).  The pastries were really good (the orange cranberry scone and the cherry danish were both really nice).  Great selection of coffee drinks and a great selection of local beers.  All in all, a really nice experience.

The absolute best breakfast in flagstaff and HANDS DOWN THE BEST PANCAKES!! The service is also always outstanding and they are great at moving tables considering they don’t take reservations. I eat here every sunday and it’s my favorite part about living in Flagstaff. A must go place!!! 11/10!

The service is absolutely amazing and the coffee is to die for. It's a cute little breakfast spot that displays art from local artists, which frequently rotates out. I always order the Baja Mocha, which is a rich chocolatey delight. I do not enjoy their food as much as their coffee because I don't like eggs, but their egg dishes are supposed to be heavenly. Definitely my favorite spot to spend my morning.

We had lunch here, as we were passing through Flagstaff. Very yummy and creative burgers! We sat outside on the lovely patio in a little square - it was a little chilly in the air, but the late-March sun kept us pretty warm. This place is right in the heart of the historic downtown. The fries were terrific! This place is amazing. Burgers were fantastic and the service was top notch! Everything about their food was delicious even down to the real ketchup and mustard. Most amazing burger I have had in while. We will be back!

I have some severely limiting food allergies and they were so accommodating! I LOVED my burger and fries. The root beer was amazing as well. The atmosphere is very fun and down to earth despite being extremely cool. When you order your food, they will recommend getting it rare, but they are good no matter how you order. Overall: food- top notch, service- top notch. I wish we had one in Phoenix!!

Diablo Burger have two veggie options, we ordered one of each. Both the veggie burger and the grilled cheese are very tasty. If I had to choose my fave from these two options it would be the grilled cheese which has an option to include an egg. Both dishes come with a huge serving of fries. Glad we stopped by.

The burger was amazing! I ordered The Marilyn and it's a medium rare burger with 2 choices of cheese lettuce, tomatoes and a pickle. And all of the good stuff is squeezed between an English muffin. Yum! The only down side was the seating. There are t tables with 6 seats inside and the rest of the seating is outdside and this time of year it's still pretty chilly.
A good burger along with very good fries. Usually a nice selection of in state beer on tap.  The meat is locally sourced. The trade off is price, but certainly worth it once and a while.

This place is start to finish amazing! The service, the food!! Where do I start! Steaks were cooked to perfection. Suggest bacon wrapped Jalapenos, filet or T-bone charred. Honestly best steaks in Flagstaff area!

Delicious, wonderful. I really like the endless and I only don't mention the steak because it is standard EXCELLENT. I missed the opportunity to rent a horse and go for a beautiful ride before dinner. Have to try it again!

Nothing bad but not great. After hearing rave reviews from several friends, and learning it is run by the same people owning Northern Pines( a great restaurant). I decided with the wife to try it again after many years. The only thing I was not disappointed in was the ah gratin potatoes( those are really good)  The steak was over cooked. We ordered med, got a steak that was med well to well done. The char finish was not the "bold" finish the server said. The salad bar was a little wilted.  The Carmel cookie?  Was uninspired, felt like a cheap rip off of Oregano's pazokie.   Service was OK but not great( i still tipped) But with a bill of right about $93? I left not particularly angry or upset, just underwhelmed.

We had some initial questions about how I wanted my steak cooked, the staff worked together to make sure I was totally satisfied. Paul the GM checked with me himself to make sure our experience was nothing less than stellar!  Highly recommend this place, hard to decide if the food is second to the customer service or if the customer service is second to the quality of the steak.

So incredibly enjoyed our dinner here. The steak was one of the bests I've ever had. Salad Bar was exceptional. Ambience is perfect and cozy and you feel like your in an old western lodge. Service was great as well. I can't wait to go back here one day❤

I was driving through and accidently found this awesome place!  I will be driving back through in a week and can't wait to stop again.  Everyone was helpful and the inventory of supplements were outstanding.  I was impressed with their raw food selection as well as the wonderful café/bakery!!!
Great stop if you are local or just passing through! Got some healthy breakfast and snacks omw to Grand Canyon!
